  "prompt": "How can I delete iPhone battery usage stats?",
  "response": "To delete or reset the battery usage statistics on your iPhone, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Reset All Settings**: This option will reset all settings but will not delete your data. Note that this will also reset Wi-Fi passwords and any customized settings.\n   - Go to **Settings** > **General** > **Transfer or Reset iPhone** > **Reset** > **Reset All Settings**.\n   - Confirm the action when prompted.\n\n2. **Check Battery Usage Stats**: After resetting the settings, the battery usage stats will be cleared. You can check them again by going to:\n   - **Settings** > **Battery**. Here you will see the battery usage statistics.\n\n3. **Restart Your iPhone**: Sometimes a simple restart can refresh the settings and statistics without needing to reset all settings.\n\nPlease note that there is currently no option to delete specific battery usage data without resetting all settings. The iPhone does not provide a granular way to delete just the battery statistics without affecting other settings.",
